Metadata-Version: 2.1
Name: simplesmtp
Version: 0.0.3
Summary: A very simple class to send e-mails using the SMTP Python Lib
Home-page: https://github.com/andidevel/simplesmtp
Author: Anderson R. Livramento
Author-email: andi.devel@gmail.com
License: Apache 2.0
Description: SimpleSMTP
        ==========
        
        A very simple class to send e-mails using the Python SMTP standard lib.
        
        Usage
        -----
        
        .. code:: python
        
            from simplesmtp import SimpleSMTP
        
            mail = SimpleSMTP(
                host='mail.host',
                username='user@mail.host',
                passw='password',
                from_email='You <youremail@mail.host>'
            )
            mail.send(to_email='email@example.com', subject='Hello', email_message='World')
        
            # Changing default from_email
        
            mail.send(
                from_email='Another From <email@example.com>',
                to_email='email@example.com',
                subject='Hello',
                email_message='World'
            )
        
            # Sending to more than one recipient
        
            mail.send(
                to_email='email1@example.com, email2@example.com',
                subject='Hello',
                email_message='World'
            )
        
            # Attachments
            
            mail.send(
                to_email='email1@example.com, email2@example.com',
                subject='Hello',
                email_message='World',
                attachments=[
                    {
                        'file': '/path/to/real/file',
                        'filename': 'the name that you want'
                    }
                ]
            )
        
        **Using SSL**
        
        .. code:: python
        
            from simplesmtp import SimpleSMTP
        
            mail = SimpleSMTP(
                host='mail.host',
                username='user@mail.host',
                passw='password',
                from_email='You <youremail@mail.host>',
                port=465,
                use_ssl=True
            )
            mail.send(to_email='email@example.com', subject='Hello', email_message='World')
        
        **HTML messages**
        
        .. code:: python
        
            from simplesmtp import SimpleSMTP
        
            mail = SimpleSMTP(
                host='mail.host',
                username='user@mail.host',
                passw='password',
                from_email='You <youremail@mail.host>'
            )
            mail.send(
                to_email='email@example.com',
                subject='Hello',
                email_message='<html> HTML source with optional embedded images ... </html>',
                msg_type='html'
            )
        
